<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-03T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="1276" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1276">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2611</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-03T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 3, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3486. Department’s instruction 3681, June 2.<note n="2" xml:id="d1276fn2">See footnote 4 to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_TWH1">Taft</persName>’s
                                latter of May 8, 1916, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_947">p. 947</ref>.</note> You may present Mr.
                                <persName corresp="#p_TWH1">Taft</persName>’s note to British
                            Government without comment.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>